race.comment: WARRIOR FOR PEACE (8) got too far back from a wide draw at Rosehill two weeks ago but powered home late to grab fourth. He's peaking now, draws a dream gate, and looks perfectly placed to land the win. SILENT CALL (2) has sharp early toe and used it to full effect at Ipswich when leading throughout. Rawiller will be positive again from the wide draw and he'll take catching. SPENZALOT (7) put it all together at Scone with a dominant display. He drops back in trip here but deserves his shot in town. HOLY HELL (4) has progressed beautifully this prep and earned her chance at this level after a soft CL2 win at Wagga. A recent Canberra trial keeps her ticking over, and with Nock's 1.5kg claim she must be respected. ULYSSES BLUE (14) meets several of these again after finishing third at huge odds at Rosehill. Gets weight relief and deserves far more respect this time. REGAL PROBLEM (10) also has claims third-up.
